# Example Cursor MCP Configuration for Lien

Add this to your Cursor settings to enable Lien MCP integration.

## For macOS/Linux

Add to: `~/.cursor/mcp.json` or project-specific `.cursor/mcp.json`

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lien": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": [
        "/absolute/path/to/lien/packages/cli/dist/index.js",
        "serve"
      ],
      "cwd": "/absolute/path/to/your/project"
    }
  }
}
```

## For Global Installation (after publishing to npm)

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lien": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@liendev/lien", "serve"],
      "cwd": "/absolute/path/to/your/project"
    }
  }
}
```

## Testing

1. Make sure you've indexed your project first:
   ```bash
   cd /path/to/your/project
   lien init
   lien index
   ```

2. Restart Cursor after adding the MCP configuration

3. In Cursor chat, try asking:
   - "Search for authentication logic" (uses semantic_search)
   - "Find similar code to this function: [paste code]" (uses find_similar)
   - "Show me context for src/index.ts" (uses get_file_context)
   - "List all functions in the codebase" (uses list_functions)

